TesterPage¶

Note that there must be as many equals signs as title characters.

Title are underlined with equals signs too¶

Subtitles with dashes¶

You can put text in italic or in bold, you can “mark” text as code with double backquote print().

Lists are as simple as in Markdown:

  • First item
  • Second item
    • Sub item

or

  • First item
  • Second item
    • Sub item

Tables are really easy to write:

Country Capital
France Paris
Japan Tokyo

More complex tables can be done easily (merged columns and/or rows) but I suggest you to read the complete doc for this :)

There are multiple ways to make links:

  • By adding an underscore after a word : Github and by adding the target URL after the text (this way has the advantage to not insert unnecessary URLs inside readable text).
  • By typing a full comprehensible URL : https://github.com/ (will be automatically converted to a link)
  • By making a more Markdown-like link: Github .
